P02-00.Name: Position control gain 1
P02-00.Description: Setting range:0-3000.0,unit:1/S The larger the parameter value,the higher the gain ratio,the greater the stiffness,the smaller the position tracking error and the faster the response.However,excessive vibration and overshoot can be caused by excessive parameters. This parameter is for steady state response.

P02-01.Name: Position control gain 2
P02-01.Description: Setting range:0-3000.0,unit:1/S The bigger the proportional gain of the position loop regulator,the bigger the parameter value,the higher the gain ratio,the bigger the stiffness,the smaller the position tracking error,and the faster the response.However,excessive vibration and overshoot can be caused by excessive parameters. This parameter is for dynamic response.

P02-03.Name: Speed feed forward gain
P02-03.Description: Setting range:0.0-100.0 The feedforward gain of the speed loop,the larger the parameter value,the smaller the system speed tracking error,and the faster the response. However,if the feedforward gain is too large,the speed loop of the system will be unstable and overshoot and oscillation.

P02-04.Name: Speed feedforward smoothing constant
P02-04.Description: Setting range:0.00-64.00,unit:ms This parameter is used to Setting the speed loop feed forward filiter time constant. The larger the value,the larger the filitering effect,but the larger the phase lag.

P02-10.Name: Speed proportional gain 1
P02-10.Description: Setting range:1.0-2000.0,unit:1Hz The greater the proportional gain of speed,the greater the servo stiffness,the faster the speed response,but too large is easy to produce vibration and noise. If the system does not generate shocks,try to increase the parameter. This parameter is for static response.

P02-11.Name: Velocity integral constant 1
P02-11.Description: Setting range:0.1-1000.0,unit:ms The smaller the Setting value is,the faster the integrating speed is,the greater the stiffness is,and the smaller the Setting value is,the easier vibration and noise will be produced. When the system does not oscillate,try to reduce the value of this parameter. This parameter is for steady state response.

P02-12.Name: Pseudo-differential feed forward control factory 1
P02-12.Description: Setting range:0-100.0,unit:1.0% When Setting to 100.0%,the speed loop adopts PI control,and the dynamic response is fast. When Setting to 0,the speed loop integral effect is obvious,which can filiter low-frequency interference,but the dynamic response is slow. By adjusting this coefficient,the velocity loop can have better dynamic response and increase the resistance to low frequency interference.

P02-13.Name: Speed proportional gain 2
P02-13.Description: Setting range:1.0-2000.0,unit:1Hz The greater the proportional gain of speed,the greater the servo stiffness,the faster the speed response,but too large is easy to produce vibration and noise. When the system does not generate shocks,try to increase the parameter. This parameter is for dynamic response.

P02-14.Name: Velocity integral constant 2
P02-14.Description: Setting range:0.1-1000.0,unit:ms The smaller the Setting value is,the faster the integrating speed is,the greater the stiffness is,and the smaller the Setting value is,the easier vibration and noise will be produced. When the system does not oscillate,try to reduce the value of this parameter. This parameter is for dynamic response.

P02-15.Name: Pseudo-differential feed forward control factory 2
P02-15.Description: Setting range:0-100.0,unit:1.0% When Setting to 100.0%,the speed loop adopts PI control,and the dynamic response is fast. When Setting to 0,the integral effect of the speed loop is obvious,which can filiter low-frequency interference,but the dynamic response is slow. By adjusting this coefficient,the velocity loop can have better dynamic response and increase the resistance to low frequency interference.

P02-20.Name: Torque feedforward smoothing constant
P02-20.Description: Setting range:0-64.00,unit:1 ms This parameter is used to Setting the torque feedforward filiter time constant.

P02-30.Name: Gain switching mode
P02-30.Description: Setting range:0-10 Setting the first and second gain switching conditions 0:Fixed as the first gain P02-00,P02-10,P02-11,P02-12. 1:Fixed to the second gain P02-01,P02-13,P02-14,P02-15. 2:Invalid DI port set to 9(gain switching input) for DI input switching:First gain is valid:second gain. 3:The torque command greater torque command is greater than the threshold(determined by P02-31 and P02-32) when switching to second gain.Less than the threshold,and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay Setting,switch to the first gain. 4:Switch to the second gain when the change of speed instruction is larger than the threshold(determined by P02-31 and P02-32).Less than the threshold,and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay Setting,switch to the first gain. 5:Speed instruction,large speed instruction is greater than the threshold(determined by P02-31 and P02-32),switching to second gain.Less than the threshold,and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay Setting,switch to the first gain. 6:Position deviation large position deviation greater than the threshold(determined by P02-31 and P02-32) switch to second gain.Less than the threshold,and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay Setting,switch to the first gain. 7:There is a location instruction that switches to second gain when there is position instruction.When the location instruction ends and the P02-33 delay is set,switch to the first gain. 8:Switch to second gain when unfinished positioning is not completed.The location is completed,and at the same time,when the P02-33 delay Setting is exceeded,the switch is switched to the first gain. 9:The actual speed is greater than the threshold(determined by P02-31 and P02-32) when switching to second gain.Less than the threshold,and at the same time exceeding the P02-33 delay Setting,switch to the first gain. 10:There are position commands and actual speeds.
